Introduction

PICKUS is an six-member project boy group under TNK Entertainment. They were formed through MBC M's survival show Fan Pick.

The group's name means "to grow together with seven members chosen by fans".

Fan Pick premiered on August 30, 2023 and the final was held on October 18, 2023, where the top seven most voted contestants became a boy group named PICKUS. The winners were, from rank one to seven, Yura, Park Mingeun, Ricky, Nam Son, Kotaro, Yoon Hyesung, and Yoo Hyeonseung.

Prior to their participation in Fan Pick, out of the seven members, Ricky was also a contestant on the survival show World Klass, and Park Mingeun was a contestant on Stars Awakening, as well as MBC's survival show Fantasy Boys.

On April 17, 2024, it was announced that Yoon Hyesung would be leaving the group and the agency, meaning PICKUS would debut as a six-member group instead.

PICKUS officially made their debut on April 23, 2024, with the release of the single album "Little Prince".

On September 26, 2024, Kotaro, Yoo Hyeonseung, and Yura were revealed as contestants on JTBC's survival show PROJECT7 starting in October 2024. Aside from that, Nam Son was also confirmed to participate on SBS and iQIYI South Korean-Chinese survival show, Starlight Boys, also starting in October 2024.
